
adding and deleting from an array:

-) array.push()   ---> add an element at the end of an array

-) array.pop()    ---> delete an element from the end 




removing inserting and extracting elements:

-) array.shift() ---> remove an element from the beginning of an array.

-) array.unshift()  ---> add one or more elements to the beginning of an array


The splice() method adds/removes items to/from an array, and returns the removed item(s):

-) array.splice(index, howmany, item1, ....., itemX)

   index = position to add/remove

   howmany = number of items to remove from  given "index" position, if set to zero no items will be removed

   item1, ..., itemX   =	Optional. The new item(s) to be added to the array


